
[1]argent

   'ARGENT, n. [L. argentum; Gr. silver, from white.]

   1. The white color in coats of arms, intended to represent silver, or
   purity, innocence, beauty, or gentleness.

   2. a. Silvery; of a pale white, like silver.

   3. a. Bright.

   Ask of yonder argent fields above.
